# 🧪 Lab: Snort IDS Rule Creation

## 🎯 Goal
Understand how signature-based detection works by creating and testing simple Snort rules.

---

# 1. Example Rules I Created

### Detect HTTP GET requests

alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"HTTP GET detected"; content:"GET"; sid:10001;)

### Detect ICMP ping

alert icmp any any -> any any (msg:"Ping detected"; sid:10002;)

### Detect suspicious user-agent strings

alert tcp any any -> any 80 (msg:"Suspicious User-Agent"; content:"curl"; http_header; sid:10003;)


---

# 2. How I Tested Them
- Made HTTP requests  
- Sent ping traffic  
- Generated custom user-agent requests using curl  

Snort logged the alerts with the rule message.

---

# 3. What I Learned
- Basic IDS rule structure  
- How signature detection differs from behavioural detection  
- How false positives happen  
- How attackers try to evade signatures  

---

# 4. SOC Relevance
Understanding IDS logic helps analyze:
- SIEM alerts  
- IPS blocks  
- Correlation rules  
- Detection evasion attempts  
